  "eprint": {
    "title": "Optimized Lattice Basis Reduction In Dimension 2, and Fast Schnorr and EdDSA Signature Verification",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Thomas Pornin",
        "email": "pornin@nccgroup",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "We present an optimization of Lagrange's algorithm for lattice basis\nreduction in dimension 2. The optimized algorithm is proven to be\ncorrect and to always terminate with quadratic complexity; it uses more\niterations on average than Lagrange's algorithm, but each iteration is\nmuch simpler to implement, and faster. The achieved speed is such that\nit makes application of the speed-up on ECDSA and EC Schnorr signatures\ndescribed by Antipa et al worthwhile, even for very fast curves such as\nEd25519. We applied this technique to signature verification in\nCurve9767, and reduced verification time by 30 to 33% on both small (ARM\nCortex M0+ and M4) and large (Intel Coffee Lake with AVX2)\narchitectures.",
    "keywords": [
      "lattice basis reduction",
      "elliptic curve",
      "curve9767"
    ],
    "category": "Implementation",
    "publication_info": "Preprint. MINOR revision.",
    "last_updated": "2020-04-20",
